post.description:
Use this endpoint to create a new synchronization on the recipient.
With this endpoint you can create a synchronization: an automatic system that allows you to create and/or update contacts.

With the `period` property you can define how often the system should synchronize data.

With the `payload` property you define the synchronization strategy. In this object you can pass all properties you would use to create an import. A synchronization is like a recursive import.

***Synchronization Limits***
- You can only create one sync per recipient
- You can create sync with `import_strategy` from `url` and `db`. The `file` strategy is not supported.

***Eg. From `url`***

You can import data from a JSON Api.

    {
        "period": "monthly",
        "payload": {
            "callback_url": "https://your-notification-endpoint.com",
            "settings": {
                "update_if_duplicate": true,
                "subscriber_status": "Subscribed",
                "triggers": {
                    "automation": false,
                    "behaviors": false,
                    "send_confirmation_email": true
                }
            },
            "import_strategy": "url",
            "import_strategy_settings": {
                "url": "http://your-source-data-url.com",
                "is_paginated": true,
                "timeout": 10000,
                "path": "data",
                "page_value": 1,
                "page_key": "page",
                "limit_value": 15,
                "limit_key": "limit",
                "response_page_key": "meta.current_page",
                "responst_total_page_key": "meta.total_pages",
                "responst_total_page_value": 1
            },
            "mapped_fields": {
                "customFieldId": "ApiPropertyInDotNotation"
            }
        }
    }


***Eg. From `db`***

You can import data from a mysql database.

    {
        "period": "monthly",
        "payload": {
            "callback_url": "https://your-notification-endpoint.com",
            "settings": {
                "update_if_duplicate": true,
                "subscriber_status": "Subscribed",
                "triggers": {
                    "automation": false,
                    "behaviors": false,
                    "send_confirmation_email": true
                }
            },
            "import_strategy": "db",
            "import_strategy_settings": {
                "host": "83.45.49.15 or http://my-db-data.com",
                "port": 3306,
                "database_name": "my_db",
                "username": "my_username",
                "password": "my_password",
                "table_name": "my_table_users",
                "condition": "",
                "columns": ["*"],
                "limit": 100,
            },
            "mapped_fields": {
                "customFieldId": "ColumnName"
            }
        }
    }

Note: username and password will be encrypted using a 256-bit security system. We will never save your credentials in clear text on our database. For this reason we cannot show you or retrieve your credentials after they have been saved.
